  "texts": [
    "VGG, Xception, ResNet, GoogLeNet, InceptionResNet, and DenseNet) to detect bone abnormalities with models trained from scratch against the same CNN architectures pre-trained using ImageNet.",
    "Furthermore, for each test dataset, two experiments were performed.",
    "After each architecture, the first experiment added a fully connected (FC) layer, and the second involved adding a sigmoid function.",
    "The overall best accuracy of 83.5% was achieved using a fine-tuned Xception architecture without an FC layer for the elbow images.",
    "For classifying shoulder images, the best result in terms of accuracy was 79.2% and was achieved using a fine-tuned DenseNet architecture with an FC layer."
  ],
